    <forecast>
        <area aac="SA_FA001" description="South Australia" type="region">
            <forecast-period start-time-local="2026-04-14T17:16:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-14T17:16:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-14T07:46:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-14T07:46:00Z">
                <text type="warning_summary_footer">For latest warnings go to www.bom.gov.au, subscribe to RSS feeds, call 1300 659 210* or listen for warnings on relevant TV and radio broadcasts.</text>
                <text type="synoptic_situation">A high pressure system centred over the south of SA will move slowly eastwards this week and a cold front will move across the far southeast of SA today followed by another cold front on Thursday. A second high pressure system is expected to follow and will become established south of the Bight late Thursday then will move eastwards during Friday and Saturday. A trough will move over the far west on Saturday.</text>
                <text type="product_footer">* Calls to 1300 numbers cost around 27.5c incl. GST, higher from mobiles or public phones.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
        <area aac="SA_PW005" description="Lower South East" type="public-district" parent-aac="SA_FA001">
            <forecast-period index="0" start-time-local="2026-04-14T15:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-15T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-14T05:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-14T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Mostly clear. Slight chance of a shower in the south later tonight. Near zero chance of rain elsewhere. Winds westerly 20 to 30 km/h becoming light in the evening.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="1" start-time-local="2026-04-15T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-16T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-14T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-15T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. The chance of morning fog in the north. Medium chance of showers in the south, slight chance elsewhere. Light winds becoming west to northwesterly 15 to 25 km/h in the morning then becoming light in the evening. Overnight temperatures falling to between 8 and 12 with daytime temperatures reaching the low 20s.</text>
                <text type="fire_danger">Moderate</text>
                <text type="uv_alert">Sun protection 9:40am to 2:30pm, UV Index predicted to reach 5 [Moderate]</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="2" start-time-local="2026-04-16T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-17T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-15T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-16T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. Very high chance of showers in the south, medium chance elsewhere. Winds north to northwesterly 15 to 25 km/h turning west to southwesterly 20 to 30 km/h in the early afternoon. Overnight temperatures falling to between 8 and 11 with daytime temperatures reaching the low 20s.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="3" start-time-local="2026-04-17T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-18T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-16T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-17T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. Slight chance of a shower in the morning. Winds southwesterly 15 to 20 km/h tending southerly 15 to 25 km/h during the morning then becoming light during the evening. Overnight temperatures falling to between 7 and 11 with daytime temperatures reaching around 18.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="4" start-time-local="2026-04-18T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-19T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-17T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-18T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Sunny. The chance of morning frost near the eastern border. Light winds becoming northeasterly 15 to 20 km/h during the morning then becoming light during the afternoon. Overnight temperatures falling to around 4 with daytime temperatures reaching around 20.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
